FBIS4-15621 "drsov069_e_94018" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 7 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Turkish Schooner Detained in Sea Economic Zone Turkish Schooner Detained in Sea Economic Zone LD0804020594 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 7 Apr 94 LD0804020594 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] The new service of Ukraine's border troops reported that a Coast Guard ship detained the Turkish schooner Bayrakhtar 20 miles from Zmiyinyy Island. The schooner was in Ukraine's exclusive sea economic zone with its tackle ready for fishing. The schooner was escorted to the frontier post in Kamyshova Bay in the city of Sevastopol to undergo full examination. In addition, a large number of fishing nets with radar beacons were discovered in the vicinity of Zmiyinyy Island. The sea border guards keep the entire Black Sea region under observation.
